Categorize a procurement item. Output JSON only with these fields:
- canonical: a clean normalized description (no SKU codes, vendor names, packaging tags, prices). If the raw description is already clean prose, copy it. Examples: "#9 SCREWS" -> "screws"; "55OZ WHIRLPAK BAGS" -> "sample bag for laboratory use"; "0w-20 oil" -> "motor oil 0w-20".
- likely_item: a one-line plain-English guess at the actual product the buyer received. Use vendor context if the description is cryptic.
- expanded_query: 3-6 search keywords for retrieving UNSPSC commodity candidates.
- primary_class_hint: the most likely UNSPSC class name (e.g., "Hardware", "Laboratory supplies", "Lubricants").
- alternative_class_hints: 1-3 plausible alternative UNSPSC class names.

INPUT:
  raw_description: {{ desc }}
  raw_category: {{ cat }}
  vendor_raw: {{ vendor_raw }}
  vendor_normalized: {{ vendor_norm }}

Never refuse. Always produce best-effort values.

PRE-CLASSIFICATION HYPOTHESIS (advisory — verify against actual candidates below; pick only from candidate codes):
  likely_item: {{ likely_item }}
  expanded_query: {{ expanded_query }}
  primary_class_hint: {{ primary_class_hint }}
  alternative_class_hints: {% for h in alternative_class_hints %}{{ h }}{% if not loop.last %} | {% endif %}{% endfor %}

INPUT:
  sku: {{ sku }}
  cat: {{ cat }}
  desc: {{ desc }}

{% if vendor_history and vendor_history | length > 0 %}{% set v = vendor_history[0] %}{% if v.served_unspsc_codes and v.served_unspsc_codes | length > 0 %}VENDOR HISTORY (this vendor has previously been confirmed for these UNSPSC codes — prefer them if a candidate matches):
{% for c in v.served_unspsc_codes %}- {{ c }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}{% endif %}UNSPSC CANDIDATES (three retrieval legs). Each candidate's level is derived from which fields are populated:
- commodity: commodity_title is non-empty
- class: class_title set, commodity_title empty
- family: family_title set, class_title empty
- segment: only segment_title set

VECTOR (cosine k-NN top-50):
{% for r in vec_rows %}- code={{ r.commodity_code }} | level={% if r.commodity_title %}commodity{% elif r.class_title %}class{% elif r.family_title %}family{% else %}segment{% endif %} | seg={{ r.segment_title }} | fam={{ r.family_title }} | cls={{ r.class_title }} | com={{ r.commodity_title }}
{% endfor %}
FTS (text match on search_tsv):
{% for r in fts_rows %}- code={{ r[0] }} | level={% if r[7] %}commodity{% elif r[6] %}class{% elif r[4] %}family{% else %}segment{% endif %} | seg={{ r[2] }} | fam={{ r[4] }} | cls={{ r[6] }} | com={{ r[7] }}
{% endfor %}
TRIGRAM (commodity_title similarity k-NN top-25):
{% for r in trgm_rows %}- code={{ r.commodity_code }} | level={% if r.commodity_title %}commodity{% elif r.class_title %}class{% elif r.family_title %}family{% else %}segment{% endif %} | seg={{ r.segment_title }} | fam={{ r.family_title }} | cls={{ r.class_title }} | com={{ r.commodity_title }}
{% endfor %}
